{
  "id": "404b8f68a94241fcb1e39db3cb9dc782",
  "title": "Infantry Fighting Vehicle - 1 : Sound System",
  "description": "IFV-1 Sound System is the result of the joint work of our experienced programmers and sound designers. Over 100 M2 Bradley engine and weapon sounds with all the necessary code",
  "longDescription": "<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/pAdCE9pterc\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>VIDEO PREVIEW</strong></a><strong> | </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/Pp9hoThrIC0\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>HOW TO USE VIDEO</strong></a> <strong>| </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/8r5OCPU2yT8\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>HOW TO USE IT FOR MULTIPLAYER</strong></a></p><p><br /></p><p>Infantry Fighting Vehicle - 1 : Sound System is an all-encompassing audio solution designed specifically for the iconic Infantry Fighting Vehicle. More than just a sound library, this product is a fully prepared package complete with the necessary code for seamless integration into the Unreal Engine, allowing you to effortlessly incorporate realistic audio into your projects.</p><p><br /></p><ul><li>Fully controllable 3d-model</li><li>The most realistic engine sounds</li><li>Different sounds from different RPMs, speed, gear and other vehicle&#39;s parameters</li><li>Weapon sounds from the weapons used by this vehicle in real life</li><li>Different sounds from different distance</li><li>Startup and Shutdown sounds</li><li>Cockpit sounds</li><li>Multiplayer Replication</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>The Infantry Fighting Vehicle - 1 : Sound System brings together a meticulously crafted collection of more than 60 engine sounds and 40 weapon sounds for Coaxial Machine Gun, 25mm Chain Gun and Missile Launcher, encompassing both exterior and interior perspectives. Experience the rumble of the engine as if you were right there on the battlefield, whether you&#39;re viewing the vehicle from the outside or seated within the cabin. Our comprehensive solution includes advanced code that dynamically adjusts sound parameters based on in-game variables such as distance from objects, vehicle speed, engine RPMs, and more not only for single-player, but also for multiplayer. This level of detail and authenticity immerses you in the world of armored combat like never before.</p><p><br /></p><p>For UE version 5.3 and below, you can download the demo scene from <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1bL-bzBI9rAVd6JwUdZyEKuESzecyKr56/view?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>. For UE 5.4 and above, the demo scene is already included in the plugin. You just need to adjust the audio settings of the project as shown in the &#39;<a href=\"https://youtu.be/Pp9hoThrIC0?si&#61;YJ-pxtS-hhV0BwMM&amp;t&#61;85\" rel=\"nofollow\">How to Use</a>&#39; video.</p>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>Code Module:Â IFV1_Sound_System (Runtime Module)</p><p>Number of Blueprints: 6</p><p>Number of C&#43;&#43; Classes: 6</p><p>Network Replicated: Yes</p><p>Supported Development Platforms: Windows</p><p>Supported Target Build Platforms: Windows</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>HOW TO USE IT WITH OUR READY-MADE SCENE: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/Pp9hoThrIC0\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>VIDEO</strong></a></p><p><strong>HOW TO USE IT FOR MULTIPLAYER: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/8r5OCPU2yT8\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>VIDEO</strong></a></p><p><br /></p><ul><li>Enable &#34;<em>IFV1_Sound_System</em>&#34; and &#34;<em>ChaosVehiclesPlugin</em>&#34; from &#34;<em>Edit &gt; Plugins</em>&#34;. Restart UE</li><li>Adjust the audio settings of the project as shown in the &#39;<a href=\"https://youtu.be/Pp9hoThrIC0?si&#61;YJ-pxtS-hhV0BwMM&amp;t&#61;85\" rel=\"nofollow\">How to Use</a>&#39; video</li><li>Open &#39;<em>DemoLevel</em>&#39; from &#39;<em>/Engine/Plugins/IFV1_Sound_System Content/DemoLevel/DemoLevel.umap</em>&#39;. For UE 5.3 and below you need to <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1bL-bzBI9rAVd6JwUdZyEKuESzecyKr56/view?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">download </a>it.</li><li><strong>DRIVE!!!</strong></li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Check <strong>IFV1_SFXComponent_BP </strong>to adjust any IVF&#39;s sound settings.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Support:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:info&#64;soundfx.studio\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>info&#64;soundfx.studio</em></a></p><p><strong>Discord:</strong> <a href=\"https://discord.gg/HzVuvSuCHr\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>https://discord.gg/HzVuvSuCHr</em></a></p>",
